✅ Real‑Time AWS VPC Issues (Production Scenarios)
🔥 Issue 1: EC2 in Public Subnet Not Reachable
Root Causes

No Internet Gateway attached
Route table missing 0.0.0.0/0 → IGW
Security Group missing inbound rule
NACL blocking traffic
No public IP attached

✅ Fix

Verify IGW
Check route table
Allow inbound (22/80/443)
Verify NACL
Attach Elastic IP / public IP


🔥 Issue 2: Private EC2 Cannot Access Internet
Root Causes

NAT Gateway missing
NAT Gateway in private subnet
Route table missing NAT entry
Elastic IP missing on NAT Gateway

✅ Fix

Create NAT Gateway in public subnet
Add route 0.0.0.0/0 → NAT
Ensure Elastic IP is assigned


🔥 Issue 3: Application Not Accessible Between Subnets
Root Causes

Security Group rules missing
Wrong subnet association
NACL blocking traffic

✅ Fix

Allow source IP / Security Group
Check inbound & outbound rules
Verify ephemeral port range (1024–65535)


🔥 Issue 4: VPC Peering Not Working
Root Causes

CIDR overlap
Route tables not updated
Security Groups blocking traffic

✅ Fix

Ensure non‑overlapping CIDRs
Add routes on both sides
Update SG rules


🔥 Issue 5: S3 Access from Private Subnet Fails
Root Causes

No NAT Gateway
No VPC Endpoint
Endpoint policy blocking access

✅ Fix

Create Gateway VPC Endpoint for S3
Update route tables
Check endpoint policy


🔥 Issue 6: VPN Connection Up but Traffic Not Flowing
Root Causes

Route tables missing on AWS side
On‑prem firewall blocking
Wrong CIDR advertised

✅ Fix

Add routes to VGW
Allow IP ranges on firewall
Verify CIDR ranges


🔥 Issue 7: Random Connectivity Drops
Root Causes

NACL ephemeral ports blocked
Asymmetric routing
Incorrect routing using multiple NATs

✅ Fix

Allow ephemeral ports in NACL
Simplify routing
Check return paths


